Among those also honoured yesterday was Achmat Isaacs. Isaacs was born in the Bo-Kaap, he was popularly known as “Big Head” and he played No 8 for Stars Rugby Club in Bo-Kaap. He also represented the Western Province Rugby Union in the 1970s. Isaacs died in June after suffering a heart attack at the the age of  69. “Achmat was a mentor to many young rugby players in the Bo-Kaap and until the time of his death he informally continued to provide encouragement and support to new generations of players,” Omar said. CAPE ARGUS